
PulseAudio is a networked low-latency → Linux/sound[sound] server for POSIX and Window systems.


"
  In a way, you can think of Pulseaudio more as a controller of ALSA than a
  preprocessor to ALSA.
" [ → http://www.troubleshooters.com/linux/sound/sound_troubleshooting.htm ]

